text.text: In the lap of the picturesque Kuttanad in Alappuzha district, situates the iconic St. Mary’s Forane Church, reflecting the Portuguese architectural style. The church dedicated to the Holy Mother was built in 1557 CE. The captivating beauty of the serene backwaters and rivers and the swaying coconut palms that adorn the banks adds to the charm of the place. Currently, the church is one of the most famous tourist attractions in Alappuzha. The church, besides its spiritual aura, also offers an enchanting environment.

text.text: My wife and I were invited to this Church today. There was a festival that evening. We were blown away by the festival, but also by the energy and enthusiasm of its congregation. These people really are filled with the Holy Spirit and seem to be living good and happy lives. I think many people in the West are really missing out on how transforming (in a positive way), Christian living and belonging to such a community can be. Our thanks to Rajeev, of the always wonderful Palma Heritage Villa, for his kind invite.

text.text:
I recently had the opportunity to visit the Moncombu Bhagavati Temple, a serene and spiritual place located in Alappuzha ,Kerala. The temple is dedicated to the goddess Parvati and is known for its unique and traditional adoration ceremony called Chathushadham.

The Chathushadham adoration at Moncombu Bhagavati Temple is a truly mesmerizing experience. The elaborate rituals and offerings to the goddess create a sense of awe and reverence among the devotees. The atmosphere during the adoration is filled with devotion and positive energy, making it a truly uplifting and spiritual experience.

Overall, my visit to the Moncombu Bhagavati Temple was a truly unforgettable experience. I would highly recommend this temple to anyone looking to immerse themselves in traditional Kerala culture and seek blessings from the divine goddess Bhagavati.

If you are offering Chathussatham, please bring the necessary large vessels( approx 4 ltr or above )for it and paper glasses to distribute the prasad to the devotees.

text.text: Serene Backwaters area of Alappuzha. Lush of greenery and backwaters. One of the unique places in Kerala. Pulinkunnu church is very famous among devotees as well as others through cinemas in different languages. Water connectivity is more preferable here. The traditionaly built old houses well maintained even after these long years adds to the beauty of Alappuzha particularly this area. Paddy & coconut are the most grown agricultural product here. Duck raising also very prominent here. Fishing is another major occupation in this area. We can rely these areas to get fresh, tasty backwater fishes and duck products here.

The temple is temporarily closed for renovation, aimed  at significantly raising its elevation to protect the temple from frequent inundation due to floods caused by rain  and high tides. The entire structure will be raised, in situ. The work is executed by an expert company in Ernakulam.

Pending renovation, the idols are being kept and rituals carried out in a sub-temple called " Balaalayam. The work may take about two years for completion.
